      body:"Demis Hassabis, Sam Altman, and Dario Amodei have each now published a plan for regulating frontier AI, and Axios finds them converging on the same diagnosis: independent testing of frontier models before public release, a standards body with authority to certify compliance and restrict dangerous systems, and US leadership over a fragmented patchwork of state or rival national regimes. Amodei goes further, pushing for an FAA-style agency with power to block unsafe launches; Altman wants an international forum for shared testing standards.",
