      title:"OpenAI ships its first hardware — Codex Micro, a $230 keypad for commanding coding agents",
      body:"Co-designed with keyboard maker Work Louder, Codex Micro is a 13-switch mechanical keypad with a rotary encoder, joystick, RGB backlighting, and 32 customizable icon keycaps, sold in clicky and silent versions. Dedicated keys accept or reject Codex changes, push-to-talk, and start new chats, while the rotary dial adjusts how many reasoning tokens a task gets. It lands the same week OpenAI is fighting Apple's trade-secrets suit over alleged AI-hardware poaching.",
