      title:"Anthropic details how it runs million-line code migrations with Claude Code",
      body:"A new claude.com engineering post describes how Anthropic staff migrated 10 code packages in the past month using Claude Fable 5, Opus 4.8, and dynamic workflows. Headline examples: Bun co-founder Jarred Sumner ported Bun from Zig to Rust — about a million lines produced in under two weeks, with 100% of Bun's existing test suite passing in CI before merge — and Anthropic Labs co-lead Mike Krieger migrated a Python codebase to 165,000 lines of TypeScript over a weekend.",
