      body:"Per a World of AI report, Google DeepMind has postponed Gemini 3.5 Pro for the third time since the original June target, citing underwhelming benchmark results — frequent hallucinations, inconsistent real-world workflows, and older checkpoints outperforming newer ones — amid researcher departures and internal frustration. No new date is confirmed (unofficial leaks now point to August); Google may ship Gemini 3.6 Flash as a temporary stopgap or shift focus to future models like Gemini 4.0 Flash.",
