      title:"Codex hits 8 million users days after GPT-5.6 — 7x growth in five months",
      body:"OpenAI's Codex passed 8 million active users (combined with ChatGPT Work) in the days after GPT-5.6's July 9 general availability — up from under 1 million weekly users in February and 5 million in early June, with the surge running 6 million by July 12, 7 million a day later, and 8 million by Sunday. OpenAI reset usage limits for all users as capacity strained; The New Stack frames the GPT-5.6-driven surge as reshaping the coding-agent competitive map.",
